{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Rename selected tracks from clipboard lines of format 'oldName, newName'\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The script will find to the 'newName' where the 'oldName' is found. I used cfillion's script Rename selected tracks from clipboard lines as a starting point. Thanks bro :)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 The input format\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The input should be in the CVS format 'oldName, newName' (without a header line)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Example:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Egill_says_goodbye, Egill_says_hello Egill_said_some_old_stuff, Egill_says_some_new_stuff\par}
